While many state governors are stepping up to meet the continuing challenges of coronavirus in unprecedented ways, our federal government continues to let us down.
Republicans want a stimulus package to include a nearly $450 billion slush fund for the Treasury Department and President Trump to hand out to ailing firms of their choosing.
Principles and policies conservatives have long held dear have been bastardized and repackaged by Trump, leaving real conservatism floating like the jetsam of a shipwreck.
Federalism is an important political model for self-governance, but not when states can’t get surgical masks and hospital gowns.
We’ll be living with the decisions we make today long after Trump is out of office.